{
  "texts": [
    "DNN adaptation Fig. 11 (bottom) depicts the estimated bandwidth values close to the actual bandwidth limits, displaying the accuracy of our bandwidth estimation.",
    "Figure 11 (top) illustrates DNN selection decisions for each client in a setting with two clients.",
    "It shows that larger DNNs are selected when the bandwidth is higher and vice-versa, implying DNN adaptation.",
    "In Fig. 11 (bottom), we observe that the error gap between estimated and actual bandwidth values increases with the actual bandwidth.",
    "Two main factors influence this error gap: (a) As we use the Linux tc utility to replay network bandwidth traces, the difference between the effective bandwidth achieved by the tc utility and the actual bandwidth widens with higher actual bandwidth values, leading to an increased error gap in the bandwidth estimation."
  ]
}